167063;instagram;2018-12-31 21:37:49;FALSE;jaha så var det dax att sammanfatta året som gått. på ett personligt plan har det inte varit något speciellt omvälvande år. det har liksom rullat på vilket iofs  är ganska skönt. allt funkar bra för mina två barn vilket är det viktigaste. och jag är plötsligt  mamma till en gymnasieelev. hjälp. hur gick det till 😁

column2: den fantastiska sommaren. jag älskade varenda varm och solig minut. och drömmer om att sommaren 2019 ska bli lika fantastisk. två fina resor kom jag också iväg på vilket jag också uppskattar otroligt mycket. hoppas få återkomma till vackra costa blanca igen ganska snart.

column1: 167069;instagram;2018-12-31 21:44:03;FALSE;no need for a sequinned dress or tropical party this new year’s eve. there’s nowhere i’d rather be tonight than with this little nugget. welcoming raffi to the family was definitely my 2018 highlight. it was a challenging year around the world so i’m choosing to focus on the positive - from the terrific global #timesup and #metoo movements to smaller moments like cuddling a tiny pug. a resolution i hope to see around the world is more kindness. why? because we can. happy new year to all of my loved ones
column2: dear friends and to my brilliant new work friends. may 2019 bring you much joy

column1: 167075;instagram;2018-12-31 22:11:14;FALSE;"right before the holidays one of my close friends took me to lunch. i shared with her some very private things from my past. i felt i was finally ready to share. she had shared very traumatic things with me over a year ago when we first met that she had experienced. so i asked her..how are you so happy? you've been through shit but you are so fun...so ""happy."" what she said...after a couple weeks of hearing it...it changed me. 'i just live my best life. i don't want to look back on my life and think it wasn't great.' honestly i struggle some days with my past trauma. here's to not giving power to the past. my therapist says it best ..'everything in your life has served a purpose

column1: 167078;instagram;2018-12-31 22:13:34;FALSE;"here are my top 9 instagram posts  for 2018. partly representative of my year

column1: it’s been all types of fun
column2: from  the highs of meeting @snoopdogg at coachella to reporting live from the royal wedding with @thismorning to the low of mother’s day without my mum. -

column1: it’s been an incredible year to be a woman 👩🏻. 100 years since women got the vote. the year of #metoo and we still have a long way to go
column3: but in 2019 may we make even bigger steps towards gender equality
column5: ethnicity equality and basically equality to all humans. -

column1: freezing my eggs and talking publicly and openly about it and getting the most amazing response from so many women who are on a similar journey has been one of my biggest lessons. a huge social epidemic that is literally about to erupt. i will continue to raise awareness. -

column1: 167127;instagram;2018-12-31 23:23:46;FALSE;"new year's eve - while a fantastic celebration of fireworks
column3: and confetti - can be an extremely difficult day for those with any form of ptsd. the booming explosion of fireworks
column4: cute kiddos next door setting off unexpected firecrackers
column5: the sudden eruption of cheers and party favors and more -- these can all be both emotionally triggering and very overstimulating to the bodies
column6: nervous systems and minds of those with posttraumatic stress.

column1: we'd love to encourage everyone with loved ones or neighbors with ptsd to check in on them
column3: and give a little extra heads up before setting anything off or popping a bottle. it can also help you both to keep in mind that they're more likely to be on-edge
column4: jumpy or irritable from all the sensory commotion around them. it's not you
column5: but they may also need you.

column3: we'd love to give you an accessible
column4: immediately-useful resource on grounding to help you stay connected to the present
column5: know where you are and when
column7: and hopefully get back to enjoying the festivities. here you go [link in bio!] beautyafterbruises.org/blog/grounding101

column1: we're coming to the end of 2018 and on reflection
column2: it's been quite the fucking year.

column1: january saw me come to the end of a shit ten month hyperemesis gravadium pregnancy that culminated in the most magical freebirth at home.

february saw a hideous month of feeding my unhappy new baby every 30 minutes while weeping round the clock and enduring two bouts of mastitis that had me hallucinating from fever. also this was the month the anxiety attacks began. the constant feeling of impending doom... the whole time still manacled to a boob barnacle who just couldn't properly feed. tongue tie was diagnosed and lola had her first tongue tie snip on the nhs.

march saw no improvement in breastfeeding but an increase in intensity in the anxiety attacks. i suffered my my third bout of mastitis and an independent lactation consultant confirmed that lola had a severe posterior tongue tie which was preventing her from feeding properly. she also had a lip tie and a high palate. her tongue tie was snipped for a second time
column2: this time by a private practitioner. the ever stoic kev described it as ""harrowing"" it was such a traumatic experience. 3 deep snips with scissors to fully release it. after all that

column1: after endless research in the early hours of the morning during april i came to the conclusion that it was possible that my 10 year old breast implants could actually be the reason that i couldn't feed my baby properly. a scan of my breasts confirmed a rupture in my left implant
column2: silicone in my lymph nodes and possibly in my milk ducts. i thought i had been poisoning my baby. i became hysterical and the post natal depression that had been tiptoeing around me since i had my baby
column3: became all encompassing. i fell face first into a pit of darkness....continued in comments

column1: 167152;instagram;2019-01-01 00:03:13;FALSE;"year in review! it was hard to leave things out from such a prolific
column2: full of learning and moving year but here we go:

column1: 1. this time last year the hollywood reporter published my oped in their power 100 women in entertainment issue (i was not one of their power 100… someday!). i was the only non-celeb featured which was pretty cool not to mention i was able to participate in the #metoo movement in a more concrete way.
2. i got married! this is me
column2: my fam and my husband’s fam shortly after we tied the knot!

column1: 4. i visited tasmania and met kangaroos! (also my now in-laws which trumps the kangaroos but i don’t have any pictures of that yet)
5.  first red carpet in a long time. of course i wore sneakers 👟
6. new friends! i am so thankful to have met and started to make friendships with the truly incredible women of the hollywood women’s collective.
7. old friends! not the best pic of me i admit but look at my friends faces. that was the first time both of them met
column2: one coming in all the way from india and the other from nyc. there were about 50 buttons and they worked together with huge smiles on their faces. what more could a girl ask for?! ❤️

column1: 8. moved into my first house with a pretty divine backyard. sometimes the sky even turns pink!
9. my platform women without borders hit 1 million women from 191 countries in the world!
phew. that’s a lot to be grateful for. i am very much looking forward 2019 with even closer friendships
column2: rewarding work and frankly some serious personal evolution! i plan to be a spiritual warrior this year!✌🏼🧚🏼‍♀️

column1: i’d like to start of this post by congratulating all of you for making it to this upcoming year.

special shoutout to all of the people who are struggling through depression/anxiety/suicidal thoughts and other mental illnesses. if you’re reading this i’m extremely happy you’re still here! it’s not an easy road but within time you’ll soon realize it will be worth it because you’re worth it! my dm’s are always open to anyone who needs a friend or just someone to vent to♥️ here’s to a new year that will teach us new lessons
column3: and loss to be able to give us better days
column4: new experiences and friendships.  which at the end of the day form us to become better people. another thing i’d like to point out is.

column2: be fearless. that’s my new years resolution. be bold
column4: take chances and become a better person. work on yourself and teach yourself that it’s ok to self love. it’s okay to feel different. it’s okay if you’re the only one in the room who got up to get seconds 🥘. our opinions of ourselves. are the only ones that are valid.

column2: it’s the media who wants to paint us as ugly. so happy new years to everyone be safe and much love from myself 💕 ( also feel free to checkout my favorite ig accounts who only send out positive energy @i_weigh @jayshetty @theellenshow ♥️)

column5: i wouldn’t change any of these events. they’ve contributed so much to who i am as a person and i think i’ve truly grown for the better. i hate to be that person *not really* but i would like to comment on our countries current political state. this year has been horrible for politics and that’s easy to see. democrat

column1: 167182;instagram;2019-01-01 00:45:32;FALSE;"happy new year and a prosperous 2019!! as we celebrate the new year let make the committed decision to be better and not bitter regardless.
to appreciate instead of hate. to give a hand up not to put down.
to bring people together and not tear people apart either with our words or deeds.
to be the shinning light this dark world really needs.
to be selfless and not selfish. to be unconditionally forgiving and not judgemental. to stand for what is right evening when it's the hardest thing to do. .
do all these this year 2019 and see what god  will do for and through you.
god bless you as you do so. be great be blessed.
one god one love one way.
but you are a chosen race

column1: 167186;instagram;2019-01-01 00:46:58;FALSE;oh me oh my. i made it through 2018. as much as it looked fun for me. i was really struggling with body image
column3: and my future goals. it didn’t hit me until the holidays came around. with the struggle of money and the inner fight or flight when it comes to harm to my family and my partner. during this
column4: i learned that i can no longer suffer in silence. it’s come to hurt me and others when i burst out and can explain it. i learned also to express my emotions more this year. i had another amazing year with james 🖤 i started my masters and learned more about film and received some amazing opportunities. i expanded on my writing and became a two time published writer. i learned
column5: it’s okay to have bumps on the road. i learned what adult fear was. i got my second baby
column6: wasabi 💚 i tried something new and cosplay with a bunch of cool girls! i almost lost a friend. i almost lost myself. i made an amazing short film about a subject i’m proud of. i also came out and shared my #metoo story. it was a roller coaster of emotions and having to be the best i could be
column8: family and my partner. i will never stop trying
column9: i will never stop fighting. here is to 2019. sorry for the long sappy post lol. i have to feel something! stay golden

column1: 167188;instagram;2019-01-01 00:49:23;FALSE;i’m someone who is never content - it’s the source of my success as much as my demise. in the reflection process of making this list

column1: 167201;instagram;2019-01-01 01:28:49;FALSE;"i’ve had one hell of a year and that’s saying something
column2: because i’ve had many bad years. this one takes the cake. one year ago today
column3: i was sexually assaulted. in my own apartment
column4: by someone i considered a friend. for.a while
column6: so i told people that i had hooked up with guy
column7: and that i regretted it and that it was my fault. because i felt so gross and violated and guilty
column8: that i didn’t know what else to say. then
column9: i finally told people the truth. not only was i sexually assaulted
column10: but i had friends and family that i opened up to completely desert me because of it. i’ve never felt more powerless and out of control in my life. i’ve never felt more terrified of men
column11: and i’ve never felt so damn small. new years is a time to celebrate
column12: to make goals and look toward the future
column13: but all i could think of this year was how to end it all. how to shut out the pain and make it go away by any means necessary. i thought he had taken everything away from me. but i’ve learned through this that there is so much in my life that i have to be grateful for. although
column14: some left my side in my time of need
column15: many stayed and loved me and were patient with me. i’ve truly learned the worth of every individual soul. i’m still trying to learn mine
column16: but i know i will find it. i’ve had a dark cloud surround me most of this year
column17: and i’m tired of it. i want to feel happy. happy is hard
column18: but i know it’s possible. i will not let one person
column19: one situation control the rest of my life. my future is bright. i have friends and family who love me unconditionally. even if i don’t feel like i deserve it. i’m not grateful for this thing that happened to me
column20: but i’m grateful for what i learned. and for the many bad years i’ve had
column21: i’ve had double that amount that were full of happiness and love. i remember them now. thank you to my family and friends who have stuck by my side. your actions truly spoke louder than words this year and i’ll never be able to thank you for it. to survivors of sexual assault
column22: i want to tell you a few things: 1. i believe you. 2. i love you. 3. we are strong. we are survivors.

column6: so i told people that i had hooked up with guy
column7: and that i regretted it and that it was my fault. because i felt so gross and violated and guilty
column8: that i didn’t know what else to say. then
column9: i finally told people the truth. not only was i sexually assaulted
column10: but i had friends and family that i opened up to completely dese me because of it. i’ve never felt more powerless and out of control in my life. i’ve never felt more terrified of men
column11: and i’ve never felt so damn small. new years is a time to celebrate
column12: to make goals and look toward the future
column13: but all i could think of this year was how to end it all. how to shut out the pain and make it go away by any means necessary. i thought he had taken everything away from me. but i’ve learned through this that there is so much in my life that i have to be grateful for. although
column14: some left my side in my time of need
column15: many stayed and loved me and were patient with me. i’ve truly learned the woh of every individual soul. i’m still trying to learn mine
column16: but i know i will find it. i’ve had a dark cloud surround me most of this year
column17: and i’m tired of it. i want to feel happy. happy is hard
column18: but i know it’s possible. i will not let one person
column19: one situation control the rest of my life. my future is bright. i have friends and family who love me unconditionally. even if i don’t feel like i deserve it. i’m not grateful for this thing that happened to me
column20: but i’m grateful for what i learned. and for the many bad years i’ve had
column21: i’ve had double that amount that were full of happiness and love. i remember them now. thank you to my family and friends who have stuck by my side. your actions truly spoke louder than words this year and i’ll never be able to thank you for it. to survivors of sexual assault
column22: i want to tell you a few things: 1. i believe you. 2. i love you. 3. we are strong. we are survivors.

column3: too many times. but it was also the year of breakthroughs. i ended my first year of college with a 3.65 gpa and finished the first semester of my second year with a 3.7. i began to love myself and my body a little more this year. i freaking posted of photo of my legs. sharing all the thickness and cellulite with strangers and friends alike. i shared my #metoo story for the first time with people who weren’t my closest family. it was a very freeing and eye opening moment. i am so insanely proud of myself because despite the setbacks and my lingering depression and anxiety
column4: i pushed through this year and i’m coming out the other side better for it. no resolutions for the new year

column1: it takes collaboration to help survivors on their journey to safety

column1: #calltosafety operates oregon’s largest #crisisline for survivors of domestic and sexual violence. and for many families who enter our emergency shelter
column2: their first call was to the incredible team at call to safety.

column1: because most survivors arrive with just the clothing on their back
column2: we provide everything from bedding to toiletries to groceries. more than 50% of our participants are children
column4: 500+ diapers in a year. thankfully the wonderful folks at @pdxdiaperbank help keep our shelves stocked with free diapers
column5: so families never have to choose between hygiene and other necessities!

column1: after families transition out of our shelter and into their own safe home
column2: we provide bedding and a kitchen kit. but it takes furniture to turn an empty space into a warm and welcoming home. that’s where our amazing friends at @communitywarehouse come in! our advocates take each survivor family to an appointment where they pick out necessities like beds

column1: 2018 has been on hell of a rollercoaster ride. i went back to my mermaid hair roots. i came out as bisexual. i pushed myself and matured professionally
column2: and i set serious goals that i'm going after
column3: come hell or high water. i learned to advocate for myself! especially medically
column4: even when i was struggling with massive amounts of progressively worsening pain.  i practiced looking towards compassion and self-love instead of self-loathing and punishment when pain and physical limitations meant gaining all the weight i'd lost over the last year (imperfectly at times
column6: i'm trying). i fell in love with jiu jitsu even if my pain and worsening physical health made me push it to the back burner (for now). i developed stronger bonds with family members and friendships flourished. i learned how to be a better advocate
column7: ally and peer. i grew as a leader. my passion for my long term goals reignited with fury
column8: and was also fueled by support from loved ones and mentors. i practiced self-love and respect by setting boundaries for my wellbeing and refused to be guilted by others' negativity
column9: shame or bullying. i let go of some of my own shame and guilt by telling the world about my sexual assaults
column10: by doing what i hate most and being vulnerable. i loved
column12: learned and lived. 2018 comes to an end with more than i thought i could handle but the last year has taught me i'm stronger and more capable than i give myself credit for. 💪

column1: 167233;instagram;2019-01-01 02:45:53;FALSE;"on this day the year 2018 will come to a close
column2: and with it the present will become the past and it’s happenings will become lessons for the future. this year the world learned and grew a lot
column3: at a pace faster than at any point in human history. we became more united. i think of our friends in eritrea and ethiopia who in june of this year signed a historic peace agreement ending years of hostile relations and opening the border once again triggering a period of mass family unification. i think of the people of north and south korea who marched together in the opening ceremonies of the 2018 olympic games in pyeongchang under the flag of a unified korea. later the leaders of both nations met for a historic summit after kim jong- un become the first north korean leader to cross the military line that divides the koreas
column4: since the end of the korean war in 1953. in 2018 the world became more compassionate. i think of the people of australia where in 2018 the nations first same sex marriages occurred. i think of philanthropist bill gates who this year donated the largest sum in history of billions from his personal fortune for a number of great causes. i think of all who learned to become more compassionate after watching “will you be my neighbour” a critically acclaimed documentary on fred rogers a respected american childrens entertainer. in 2018 the royal family of canada
column5: the u.k. and the commonwealth grew. in may prince harry married the lovely meghan markle becoming the duke and duchess of sussex and announced later in the year that they were expecting their first child. in april the duke and duchess of cambridge welcomed their third child into the world to be named prince louis of cambridge. in october princess eugenie of york married her partner jack brooksbank to fanfair across the united kingdom. in 2018 we learned from our failures and grew from tragedies. i think of the brave woman who stood up around the world as a part of the #metoo movement calling out men for inappropriate and abusive behaviour. continued in comments: #theworldin2018 #last2018post

column8: the u.k. and the commonwealth grew. in may prince harry married the lovely meghan markle becoming the duke and duchess of sussex and announced later in the year that they were expecting their first child. in april the duke and duchess of cambridge welcomed their third child into the world to be named prince louis of cambridge. in october princess eugenie of york married her partner jack brooksbank to fanfair across the united kingdom. in 2018 we learned from our failures and grew from tragedies. i think of the brave woman who stood up around the world as a part of the #metoo movement calling out men for inappropriate and abusive behaviour. continued in comments: #theworldin2018 #last2018post

column2: #untouchable. i’ve recently on many occasions sat on the front line of old familiar war zones. teetering on a knifes edge where i can taste old familiar habits and still
column3: i choose spiritual health and physical wellness to the best of my ability for where i’m at. this is #progress. this is not an easy place to arrive at for anyone
column4: and certainly not for me! #self #sabotage used to be my #jam baby! but now i can thrive in this danger zone and use it as a place where i get to check my foundation
column5: and check in with my purpose. my #absolute #desire to #serve a #higher #purpose. to go #within and #draw from my experiences and offer a hand to anyone who needs it. don’t be afraid of the darkness within. use it as fuel! i take my spiritual life very seriously
column6: i also do not forget where i came from and those still stuck in the fight. ayurveda and yoga philosophy has me rising from the rubble like a phoenix and sometimes i meet others on the front line just waiting for someone to ask them to rise with me. i made an #unexpected and #incredible #connection last night that reminded me of exactly why i do what i do. so thank you god for putting me exactly where i needed to be as always. #canthurtme 📷 @yanvh;;en;#boss

column1: 167300;instagram;2019-01-01 05:22:56;FALSE;"i started this year with a personal project in support of the broken hearts club.

these are a few samples from the #1kbrokenhearts series. a process that was mostly about personal healing and catharsis in the wake of being excommunicated from my extended family when i refused to stay silence about some very ugly secrets i discovered five years ago.
at the time it turned my whole world upside down and i struggled daily with the question of what was the right path. now
column3: i am so grateful that i made it out of that $***show in one piece and am blessed enough to know that the sacrifice and rejection i faced
column4: means my kids can begin a new legacy of wholeness and truth.

column1: now that i'm on the other side i can't believe i ever doubted what my heart knew i had to do.
if you're ever faced with a choice between comfort and an ugly truth
column2: choose truth no matter what it costs. i can tell you without a doubt you'll look back years later and be glad you did.

column1: 167336;instagram;2019-01-01 07:00:11;FALSE;"2018 astrological review - dissolving conflict and duality
i’m not usually one for being with the crowd
column2: but i think we can all agree collectively that 2018 has been a year that can only be experienced once. like a novelty. or that creepy uncle who’s best admired from afar. like now that you learned what’s in that haunted house
column4: am i right? let’s hope you learned the lessons
column5: otherwise saturn will take care of that. 😉

column2: early this year saturn had just barely entered the sign of capricorn
column3: and boy was the weather frigging cold. father time came along and blew his icy need to make you work and sucked out any possible sense of joy. as if that wasn’t enough
column4: there was also a conjunction to mars and jupiter in scorpio. jupiter likes to make everything it touches nice and big
column6: as a sign that keeps her cards to her chest. conjunct mars meant a lot of secrets and the shadow side of the masculine came to light.

column2: a lot of you probably found the usual aloofness encouraged by our lovely saturn-ruled world just didn’t work for you anymore. you were forced to open and grow. you were forced to drop the armour. it probably caused conflicts in love. you probably even pushed away someone special
column3: thinking you were protecting yourself. venus on the other the hand got to be all about business in capricorn
column4: conjunct black moon lilith. 😈💋 lilith decided that the feminine would take no more shit and get to work
column5: and on the sun meant you couldn’t ignore her raw beauty. she stopped playing the whole virgin/vixen dynamic and decided to get real. she was bare to see whether you wanted to or not. and venus square rebel buddy uranus- giving her a more unconditional side to her feminine wiles. #timesup #metoo and whatever hashtags and beyond. she’s a temple and she demands to be worshipped for the goddess she is.

column1: with saturn in opposition to the moon- and in gemini
column2: the sign of duality (masculine/feminine) meant there was a push-pull between our inner duality vs. everyone else. you probably spent much of the year feeling lonely and misunderstood. power struggle was one of (continues in comments)";;en;#timesup

column1: 167347;instagram;2019-01-01 08:01:49;FALSE;museum of 2018 by #theskimm features the major events that have happened this year. i’ll be honest
column2: 2018 was a rough year for me. chaos of the world aside
column3: i struggled with some depression due to issues with my health
column4: trauma from my past and negative events that impacted my loved ones. even though there was much adversity this year
column5: i’m proud of the accomplishments i made. i channeled #destinyschild by becoming an independent woman
column6: i found the courage to use my voice to stand up for myself and my body
column7: i educated myself about social issues and i attended safe spaces for marginalized groups. 2018 wasn’t perfect but i have grown so much as a person and i learned so much about the world and myself because of the events that have transpired this year. some of the big goals that i hope to accomplish for 2019 is to forgive myself
column8: accept my body regardless of my size and saying yes to opportunities. happy new year! #independentwomen #throwyourhandsupatme #mybodymyrules #metoo #futureisfemale;;en;#theskimm

column1: 167377;instagram;2019-01-01 09:33:23;FALSE;"to everyone who lived with #depression #anxiety #ptsd #sexualtrauma #trauma #mentalillness and #addiction in 2018 and who thought about killing themselves but didn’t- i see you
column3: understand how hard it can be to stay alive and love you & see your bravery. it was a tough
column5: #triggering year for many of us. #metoo and #feminism raised everyone’s consciousness & many of us had to deal with having our trauma triggered and facing the fear of speaking up and being seen. having a president who is a sexual predator and who clearly used his power & privilege to not face consequences and to silence women; whilst his paid servants now face prison
column6: that is very uncomfortable for many of us. his candidate for supreme court looked like any of the shifty guys many of us have encountered- men who can’t handle their booze and do gross things to others; and often in blackout . whereas #drchristineblaseyford had the courage & the dignity to stand up before the nation; and then not be believed. when we all knew she was speaking the truth. in 2019 i urge that we start to see the many men who are also survivors of sexual & physical violence at the hands of other men & women; and who get tarred with the same brush as a potential abuser or colluder with the patriarchy. may 2019 be a year of happiness & light and an opportunity to start healing our relationships with ourselves & all the others. 🙏🏽 i am so happy to have made it out of 2018 alive 🎉 and hope 2019 is the year we start to protect #intersex babies & children & give us our human right to bodily integrity & gender choice including #nonbinary #suicide #suicidal #hope #itgetsbetter";;en;#depression

column1: 167471;instagram;2019-01-01 13:28:57;FALSE;"rani mukherji had some rather strong opinions within the annual round table by rajeev masand. during the discussion regarding the #metoo movement
column2: she stated that girls are responsible for their own protection. girls should learn martial arts to protect themselves. -

column1: it infuriated many viewers as the statement was completely ignorant . deepika padukone and alia bhatt had conflicting feelings regarding her statement.
how do you feel about what was said?

column2: it shouldn't even get to the point where self-defense is necessary. harassment should not be happening . it happens in various settings and martial arts is surely not the only way to avoid it. why should women have to learn to ""protect"" themselves when men harass them.. harassment shouldn't be happening in the first place. once again
column3: the blame is put on the victim as a lack of ""protection"".

column1: it happens in households as well. not everyone has the strength to fight it alone
column2: that's why people stand together regarding the movement.

column2: i hate character limits.  part ii 😜

the more growth i experienced and the more challenges i placed in front of myself to overcome...and here i am.  i'm grateful for every challenge that has been placed in front of me and every trauma that has been experienced because i've been blessed with the ability to overcome them and i'm still alive.  i am also now blessed to watch clients make their own progress with the same steps i took years ago to become stronger and healthier.  bring it on 2019!! 💪 i hope everyone goes full beastmode towards a better life this year!!

column3: involves a lot of words. two books released: jesus every day and the #7deadlyfriendships. column4: but ended with strength. and the very thing i did not want to be known for (sexual abuse) became the platform god ushered in on the wings of #metoo. it’s bittersweet

column1: 167507;instagram;2019-01-01 14:50:28;FALSE;"【prはなぜ難しい？　人々にとって「どっちでもよいこと」が、インサイトで「自分ごと」になる】- pr発想事例
一定の水準以上を収めている企業であれば決定的な差はない。prする対象が多くの人にとって「どっちでもよいこと」。prにおいては、その「どっちでもよいこと」を広く話題にして、最終的に「それはよい！」と思わせることがミッション。そんな悩みはどうすれば解決できるのか？
ここでインサイトが出番となる。
声高に自らの優位性を語ったとしてもほとんどの受け手には響かない。そこで必要なのが、自らのブランドや商品、企業を離れて、「人間を見に行く」こと。ブランドや企業との関係性を出発点にするのではなく、純粋に「ターゲットの興味関心事」に寄り添い、その人々が興味や関心を持っていることを探す。

prに関わる人ならよくご存じの事例、カンヌライオンズ2017のpr部門でグランプリを獲得した「fearless girl（恐れを知らない少女）」。 「fearless girl」のクライアントは投資ファンドの企業です。資金を預ける側にとって、投資ファンド会社はどのように感じられているのか。確かにパフォーマンスの差は全くない訳ではないが、一定の水準以上を収めている企業であれば決定的な差があるとも思えない。先ほどの「どっちでもよい」状況である。従って、声高に自らの優位性を語ったとしてもほとんどの受け手には響きかない。そこで必要なのが、自らのブランドや商品、企業を離れて、「人間を見に行く」こと。
言葉にならないもののそのことに無意識に感じている良さやポジティブな感情を探り出す。これがすなわち「どのような価値を感じているか」というインサイトだ。「fearless girl”の例でいえば、「女性と男性の社会的な格差」が人々の関心事として存在し、まず「同じ人間同士なのに男女に差があることは納得いかない」という認識がある。

そして、女性の社会的地位について持論を述べたシェリル・サンドバーグ（facebookのcoo）の「lean in」が全米のベストセラーになる、あるいは後に「#metoo」として結実する、被害者によるセクシャルハラスメントの告発が始まる（2015年10月には既に女優のアシュレイ・ジャッドらが加害者の名を出さずにインタビューで業界内でのセクハラの問題を語っていた）、といった事象から、「理不尽な現状にあっても、まっすぐな心で立ち向かうことは素晴らしい」といった人々のインサイトを、制作者たちが読み取ったと推測される。
ピュアな勇気や力を気持ちのよいものだという心理が、無意識の領域にあるのだ。 【優れたpr企画例】
1.「人間を見に行く」ことで、人々の興味関心事に関するインサイトを見つけだす。2.見つけたインサイトとprの対象であるものとの接点を見出す(ブランドの持つファクトとそのインサイトを結びつけること）3.ブランドを離れた「人間」の関心事に関する心理にアイデアが結びつく 【失敗するpr企画例】

1.ブランドや商品について、人々がどのように感じているか、考えているかを調べる。2.その感じ方や考えに基づいて、ブランドや商品起点のアイデアを考える。3.ブランドや商品からのジャンプや広がりがない表層的なアイデアが生まれ、人々の心を動かせない。メディアにも新鮮味が感じられないので取り上げられない。";;en;;;;;;0;;mountain_ad;ヤマザワケンタ;;0;False;0;0;0;3;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/4bc1042a0325ef82149122f917c7b40a/5D029A69/t51.2885-15/e35/47694710_218883198992522_5133843048822781139_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"【prはなぜ難しい？　人々にとって「どっちでもよいこと」が、インサイトで「自分ごと」になる】- pr発想事例

ピュアな勇気や力を気持ちのよいものだという心理が、無意識の領域にあるのだ。 【優れたpr企画例】 1.「人間を見に行く」ことで、人々の興味関心事に関するインサイトを見つけだす。2.見つけたインサイトとprの対象であるものとの接点を見出す ( ブランドの持つファクトとそのインサイトを結びつけること）3.ブランドを離れた「人間」の関心事に関する心理にアイデアが結びつく 【失敗するpr企画例】 1.ブランドや商品について、人々がどのように感じているか、考えているかを調べる。2.その感じ方や考えに基づいて、ブランドや商品起点のアイデアを考える。3.ブランドや商品からのジャンプや広がりがない表層的なアイデアが生まれ、人々の心を動かせない。メディアにも新鮮味が感じられないので取り上げられない。;【prはなぜ難しい？ 人々にとって「どっちでもよいこと」が、インサイトで「自分ごと」になる】- pr発想事例 一定の水準以上を収めている企業であれば決定的な差はない。prする対象が多くの人にとって「どっちでもよいこと」。prにおいては、その「どっちでもよいこと」を広く話題にして、最終的に「それはよい！」と思わせることがミッション。そんな悩みはどうすれば解決できるのか？ ここでインサイトが出番となる。 声高に自らの優位性を語ったとしてもほとんどの受け手には響かない。そこで必要なのが、自らのブランドや商品、企業を離れて、「人間を見に行く」こと。ブランドや企業との関係性を出発点にするのではなく、純粋に「ターゲットの興味関心事」に寄り添い、その人々が興味や関心を持っていることを探す。 prに関わる人ならよくご存じの事例、カンヌライオンズ2017のpr部門でグランプリを獲得した「fearless girl（恐れを知らない少女）」。 「fearless girl」のクライアントは投資ファンドの企業です。資金を預ける側にとって、投資ファンド会社はどのように感じられているのか。確かにパフォーマンスの差は全くない訳ではないが、一定の水準以上を収めている企業であれば決定的な差があるとも思えない。先ほどの「どっちでもよい」状況である。従って、声高に自らの優位性を語ったとしてもほとんどの受け手には響きかない。そこで必要なのが、自らのブランドや商品、企業を離れて、「人間を見に行く」こと。 言葉にならないもののそのことに無意識に感じている良さやポジティブな感情を探り出す。これがすなわち「どのような価値を感じているか」というインサイトだ。「fearless girl  の例でいえば、「女性と男性の社会的な格差」が人々の関心事として存在し、まず「同じ人間同士なのに男女に差があることは納得いかない」という認識がある。 そして、女性の社会的地位について持論を述べたシェリル・サンドバーグ（facebookのcoo）の「lean in」が全米のベストセラーになる、あるいは後に「etoo」として結実する、被害者によるセクシャルハラスメントの告発が始まる（2015年10月には既に女優のアシュレイ・ジャッドらが加害者の名を出さずにインタビューで業界内でのセクハラの問題を語っていた）、といった事象から、「理不尽な現状にあっても、まっすぐな心で立ち向かうことは素晴らしい」といった人々のインサイトを、制作者たちが読み取ったと推測される。 ピュアな勇気や力を気持ちのよいものだという心理が、無意識の領域にあるのだ。 【優れたpr企画例】 1.「人間を見に行く」ことで、人々の興味関心事に関するインサイトを見つけだす。2.見つけたインサイトとprの対象であるものとの接点を見出す ( ブランドの持つファクトとそのインサイトを結びつけること）3.ブランドを離れた「人間」の関心事に関する心理にアイデアが結びつく 【失敗するpr企画例】 1.ブランドや商品について、人々がどのように感じているか、考えているかを調べる。2.その感じ方や考えに基づいて、ブランドや商品起点のアイデアを考える。3.ブランドや商品からのジャンプや広がりがない表層的なアイデアが生まれ、人々の心を動かせない。メディアにも新鮮味が感じられないので取り上げられない。

column2: the fundraiser has brought in over 22 million dollars. the time’s up legal defense fund
column4: is administered by the national women’s law center and was founded by a group of hollywood celebrities in the midst of the #metoo movement which has swept the country to become a household name. the aim of time’s up is to provide legal assistance to people who step forward to report workplace harassment. as of april 2018
column6: 500 people had reached out to the project for legal help
column7: a number that has undoubtedly increased since then.

column1: i’m thankful for it. because it’s taught me compassion

at this moment. go forth into 2019 empowered and with vision

column1: 167530;instagram;2019-01-01 15:36:17;FALSE;"first workout of 2019!!! man did i feel that taco salad from last night 😂😂 but the work-out was completed none the less 👍
i'm not going to write out a huge 2018 reflection followed with a long 2019 goal... i'll keep it short and sweet
2018 taught me a lot... as should every year!  i am grateful for the victories and humbled by the failures
i lived with no regrets and will continue to do so throughout the new year
i will take my failures of 2018 and use them to propel my future and career in 2019
every day is a fresh start and a new day to make it as you want... every time you have desire and drive to change

column1: 2018 was an insanely amazing rollercoaster of personal
column3: friendships and family adventures. a horrific move end of 2017 from la to sf for a 3 month life lesson in “wtf am i doing at this shit show brand of batshit crazies + a crash course in navigating and surviving a made up #metoo attack at the height of #metoo that ended with the crazies telling me
column4: oh well we couldn’t make that lie stick cuz you have a proven track record as a champion of women and oh your a big homo but hold on we have something else just as crazy
column7: idiotic and outrageous so let’s go with it!! yeah bye! but you know what two of the most incredible and amazing things happened 1. the universe shot me full circle right back into the family biz and working with my insanely talented husband(and smoking hot) to help him build his dream and his brand. (look at us now!) and 2. it built an iron clad understanding and bond between us that made 2018 family first and building our future
column8: i believe 200% that the universe has a plan and she works hard to get you to pay attention and if you listen and follow the signs you can experience the beauty of knowing exactly who you are
column10: how to love yourself and others honestly
column11: what your true worth is and what your purpose and passions are.  i fucking love my life
column14: my family and friends and everything my life has become
column15: zero regrets or take backs. 2019 for me is about owning my truth
column21: really listening not to just listen and blowing up #peaceoutskincare globally! i wish everyone a kickass 2019 with love

column2: it wasn’t as crazy as my 2017 (and for that i have to be thankful!) but nonetheless it’s never going to be the *smoothest* ride when we’re allowing someone else to be the pilot 👩‍✈️ 👨‍✈️. i know there are a lot of memes about a new year being a joke blah blah blah but i truly believe that it’s a chance at a fresh start—or at least steps closer towards one! a half inch of progress a day is still progress. so thank you
column3: because all of you truly helped me get through this past year and here’s to a new one on the books! 😘💜🥂

column1: i've survived 38 weeks of this pregnancy! i survived 2018. it would be a lie to say 2018 was anything but exhausting and exciting. i was able to find my inner strength and live outside of my comfort zone. i was able to grow and evolve.

we celebrated 1 year with maddox and changed our entire life for piper. we celebrated hillside fitness opening and cried a little closing it. i have struggled through this pregnancy from the beginning and am so grateful for a new year and new addition to our family.
2019 is the year of the feminine. universal 3 year is a conscious reminder to be aware of the 3 aspects of your being and align your ‘mind
column2: body & soul’ in the direction of love and light... to become a source of possibility in your life.

column2: birth our creativity (doing what turns you on)
column3: and engage with the world using all your senses.  she will encourage us to not stay small & hide away from the world
column4: but rather errogenously engage in every facet of birthing a new world – a ménage à trois of joy

column1: on the day that you died
column2: i was only 12. i wish i could’ve shook your shoulders to lift your eyelids and awaken your voice.

column1: on the day that your hands explored my body and your hot breath counted down the seconds in my ear
column2: i was only 16. i wish i could’ve hurt you
column3: stopped you. i wish i could’ve told somebody.

column1: on the day that you told me that you would never love me
column2: i was 22. i wish i could’ve erased every midnight kiss and snipped every silver lining that my therapist prescribed.
but somehow the pain grew into a powerful mosaic inside of me. i let it speak. i let it shine. i let it inspire.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: 167657;instagram;2019-01-01 18:43:46;FALSE;"🇵🇹mulher. mãe. irmã. filha. amiga. se elas não existissem
column2: o nosso mundo não seguia para a frente! a associação corações com coroa tem como um dos seus objetivos contribuir para a igualdade de género
column3: como estratégia eficaz no combate á pobreza e á exclusão social. esse apoio passa por atribuir bolsas de estudo a raparigas que se encontram em risco de não poderem prosseguir os seus estudos. na mudança do ano
column4: façam a diferença e tornem os sonhos de alguém realidade. pequenos gestos mudam o mundo! bom 2019! 🇬🇧woman. mother. sister. daughter. friend. if they didn’t exist

column1: 167744;instagram;2019-01-01 21:02:41;FALSE;these are my favorite movies from 2018. by no means are these the best movies of the year
column2: they’re just my favorites. i’ve always said movies don’t surprise me much anymore. well these are the movies that someway or another surprised me in a good way this year. from the amazing atmospheric and very scary #hereditary with a great unforgettable turn by #tonicollete to a #spiderman that bested most of the comic book and super hero movies this year of course not including the great #blackpanther with the best #marvel villain to date and of course we need to mention the outstanding quasi sarah connor turn by the talented #jamieleecurtis in #halloween and the female empowerment and #metoo message from #widows #assassinationnation #blockers #oceans8 #missionimpossiblefallout #aquietplace #birdbox and more. what a great year for horror
column4: netflix lol and more than anything for strong women in movies this year! whether you were a matriarch protecting your family from unseen or extraterrestrial creatures like #emilyblunt or #sandrabullock or women fighting for their place in a make dominated world like the ones in widows
column6: a scientist looking for her husband with a female crowd in #annihilation
column7: the strong women in #avengers or the teens in #an
column8: well strong strong female characters all around. oh and also #lovesimon which even though it was a #lgbt movie was the most refreshing coming of age and romantic movie of the year in my opinion. alright that’s that! check them out people! 🖤😬😱 p.s- sorry disney and pixar. your animation wasn’t surprising in any way this year.;;en;#hereditary

column1: 167746;instagram;2019-01-01 21:03:18;FALSE;"i love that my #bestnine2018 includes all 3 recent photo series as well as best friend @bishopkb and the women’s march ✊🏼📸 dichotomies
column3: tells the story of the stages of singledom and relationships through poetry and photography. unheard
column5: is a multimedia performance that gives voice to the women throughout history and mythology who’s stories have been overshadowed by the stories of the men around them. sass the patriarchy
column6: a collaboration with @celinepinget was shot for @thiswaynorth ‘s #sassthepatriarchy
column7: an all female concert that tours the world and includes panel discussions with local musicians about how to empower women in the music industry 🎶🎵 it wasn’t long ago that i associated being feminine with being weak and wanted to be ‘one of the guys’ so i could fit into the very male dominated industry’s i wanted to work in. once i learned that being feminine is being strong (it truly is) thats when i found true joy and true inspiration (and so many photos!). i look forward to more projects like this - so if you’re a creative or visionary with an idea for a series with a real message please connect with me!

column1: 167751;instagram;2019-01-01 21:05:55;FALSE;"my mood going into 2019... so 2018 was a year of some highs and quite a few lows. i learned a lot about myself and the people around me. i learned that self worth is so important
column2: and i cannot stress that enough. i learned how to put myself first. that is how i got through the past year. i have to thank my wonderful friends and family who helped me through very difficult times this year. i thank you all
column4: who held me when i was crying
column5: who brought me on spontaneous trips
column6: who just loved me for who i am. thank you. 2018 was hell
column7: but i learned who can be in my life and who cannot. i learned how to hold people an arms distance away
column8: which is ok for your own recovery. you’re not gonna be best friends with everyone
column9: and that’s ok. i hope 2019 has a few more highs
column10: but i will forever remember 2018 as a year of recovery

column9: and that’s ok. i hope 2019 has a few more highs
column10: but i will forever remember 2018 as a year of recovery

column2: emportant avec elle de magnifiques souvenirs; allez chercher mon père au bc pour qu’il emménage tout près de chez moi fût tout un défi pour moi et la réalisation d’un rêve inimaginable.

column1: rétablir les liens brisés avec ma sœur après 6 ans de silence radio a été pour moi...........désolée
column2: incapable pour moi de trouver le mot idéal pour décrire cette situation tellement inattendue mais combien vitale! ✌🏻

column1: les 2 meilleures choses que la vie pouvait m’apporter . merci 🙏🏻 2018!
ceux qui me connaissent savent à quelle point la famille pour moi
column2: c’est d’une importance capitale. ma meute
column3: que je protège comme une louve n’était pas complète sans ces deux personnes qui en font partie intégrante. dans cette meute bien garnie se trouve aussi un louveteau différent des autres. le plus âgé de tous
column4: qui nous occasionne bons nombres de tracas et de stress mais qui nous fait aussi réaliser en même temps à quel point une mère protège et aime ses petits quoi qu’il advienne et ce
column5: inconditionnellement ❤️ en emmenant parfois quelques soucis de santé. je prends soin de moi 🧘🏻‍♂️ le 4 janvier 2018 j’ai pris mon courage à 2 mains et j’ai dénoncé celui qui m’a pris mon enfance! la vague #metoo a été pour moi une délivrance d’un poids énorme sur mes épaules. je suis fière de l’avoir fait même si ça brise des secrets de famille. c’est moi qui marchera dorénavant la tête haute!

column1: que 2019 protège ma meute et veille à ce que chacun d’entre eux aie une année remplie de défis stimulants et aussi réalisables les uns que les autres qui forgeront ensuite leur expérience
column5: estime de soi pour devenir des personnes accomplies et qu’ils vivent leur vie en ayant des bases solides.

column3: qui veille tout comme moi au confort
column6: bonheur de la meute merci pour tout ce que tu fais pour nous tous. sans toi

column1: famille et amis privilégiés dans notre vie je vous souhaite à tous une très belle année 2019 🥂 mettez vos vieilles rancunes de côté et tournez la page
column4: mettez vos cellulaires de côté et regardez vous dans les yeux
column6: emportant avec elle de magnifiques souvenirs; allez chercher mon père au bc pour qu’il emménage tout près de chez moi fût tout un défi pour moi et la réalisation d’un rêve inimaginable.

column1: 167760;instagram;2019-01-01 21:11:01;FALSE;"new years day is always a day of reflection for me. it’s been 9 years since i survived my first suicide attempt. 2018 brought back a lot of the memories that led to that moment by having my rape case reopened but this time i came out stronger. it was a year of learning
column2: growth and self acceptance. although charges were ultimately dropped
column3: i learned i am not defined by what happened to me. i found my sense of purpose through advocacy work with mental health minnesota
column4: talked about the injustice survivors face to the associated press and stood strong with other survivors for the star tribune. i will continue to advocate for myself and others in 2019
column5: as well as grow. i wish i could go back and hug that sad 17 year old and tell her it does get better
column6: you’ll be glad you are still here ♥️ here’s to another year of loving

column1: 167763;instagram;2019-01-01 21:40:53;FALSE;"qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv
column2: completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

column1: that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing
column2: just part of the story we are all interacting with.

column1: the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters
column2: then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

column1: that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics
column3: and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters
column4: so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

column1: 167774;instagram;2019-01-01 21:47:33;FALSE;"former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel
column2: but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

column1: in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23
column2: flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia
column3: and kushner spoke with kim darroch
column4: the british ambassador to the united states
column5: according to diplomats familiar with the conversations
column6: who spoke on condition of anonymity.

column1: the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump
column2: who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric
column3: took office on jan. 20. it failed
column4: with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

column1: the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move
column2: egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution
column3: prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

column1: a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a ""high level"" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.
according to court documents made public on friday
column2: a member of trump's presidential transition team
column3: later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner
column4: told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments
column6: to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

column1: 167800;instagram;2019-01-01 22:31:14;FALSE;"can we put it to rest already 😑
it is diagnosable. it is treatable. it is not curable. just like most people with any sort of behavioral “issues” or even anyone with addictions
column2: they must want to change. a narcissist can control their behavior
column3: they just generally choose not to. .

column1: my husband has gone through “epiphanic” moments when he says he’ll change. it lasts a week
column2: maybe two. at first this newfound change felt good
column3: like i finally got through to him! but as the years went on and i realized that this was just a pattern of behavior
column4: i stopped believing it and didn’t count on anything to last. .

column1: so tell me: why has he been on his best behavior for nearly three months? yes
column3: i will document those slip ups on here. but to be honest
column4: i’ve been posting a lot of facts and memes and quotes because there hasn’t been much at all to document. when he does slip and the mask drops
column5: it’s brief. he apologizes. he’ll show me he’s sorry by taking care of dinner
column8: etc. he will watch my shows with me
column9: not give me hell for being on my phone
column10: he’s given me control of the finances...for christmas
column11: he wasn’t invited to my family’s house yet he wanted me to go

column7: we celebrate and we affirm. in most recent years black people ( aka #blacktwitter) have  used social media to highlight and start conversations around the things that matter the most to us- from politics to the next viral dance challenge ( i.e.  #whatblackpanthermeanstome #rootingforeverybodyblack #youoksis  #bringbackourgirls #blacklivesmatter #metoo #sogonechallenge #onthatdickchallenge #blackgirlmagic). we make black history happen each and every day with a single hashtag

column1: last year was “remember”. and looking back i can see the power of this prayer by its unique

column2: i want to share with you something very personal and intimate that happened and that only my close friends know about.

column1: as i set this intention in january 2018
column2: i was going to embark on a long sexual trauma practitioner training and tantric exploration.
when during a training and practice session i discovered (i remembered) that i was sexually abused by a few men when i was a child #metoo.

column1: the trauma memory was in the depth of my body
column2: hidden from my conscious mind. needless to say
column3: that the experience was very intense and yet i discovered
column4: in the horror of the trauma
column5: the blessing it brought for my path and my calling.

column1: it allowed me to finally understand so many of my behaviors
column2: from my fear (and anger) towards powerful & strong men
column3: to my capacity to feel an infinite depth of empathy for sexually abused people.

column1: i also felt immense gratitude for the close friends who showed up during that time to hold me and realized how essential it was/is in my healing process (as it is for all trauma victims). i felt also that the past 15 years of deep spiritual work
column2: allowed me to be able to hold my trauma in a container of light

column1: so this year my word is intimacy.

column1: 167902;instagram;2019-01-02 02:46:20;FALSE;2018 gave me the the honour of attending 11 deliveries of 11 healthy babies! nine of these babies were born to first-time parents and one was a vbac at the @torontobirthcentre. in the summer
column2: i had the great privilege of travelling to tennessee to learn directly from @thefarmmidwives
column4: where i took my midwife assistant training and where birth is viewed as a normal
column7: i did not get into ryerson’s midwifery program but was one of 115 interviewed and i’ll try again in 2020. that same week
column8: i learnt the true meaning of “informed consent” and the #metoo movement when a healthcare provider sexually assaulted me. my healing journey has been difficult and it has broken my heart to see women disrespected in similar ways during birth. i’ve been frustrated with the system for not prioritizing advances in women’s health
column9: and i’ve been enraged to witness healthcare providers who do not follow evidence-based practices and breed fear of birth in our communities. the fire inside me has grown stronger and propels me to continue fighting for women’s rights - especially during birth - in 2019. the year ahead brings many great possibilities. i’ll be expanding the use of music therapy in my practice and hope to conduct a children’s choir. i will continue travelling and researching strategies that are used around the world to improve childbirth. i will continue to support families who choose hospital births and home births. i will encourage women to choose @ontariomidwives as their healthcare providers for optimal outcomes
column10: as the quality of care i’ve observed is much higher. my buddhist and yoga practices will continue to give me the courage and compassion i need to support families during the childbearing years and stand tall in the face of injustices. i will fight with love for #evidencebasedbirth and i’ll support my clients in the decisions they make. i’ll continue to be with women
column12: through thick and thin. i pray that all babies born in 2019 will have beautiful beginnings. for when life starts with peace

column1: 167938;instagram;2019-01-02 04:01:52;FALSE;"check out @richroll stories for some wonderful inspiration about sobriety
most people learn about sobriety in a hard and painful way
column2: usually there is a dui or job loss and a tremendous amount of pain and sobriety is forced upon them.

column1: i am forever grateful for the opportunity to learn about sobriety from rich and @glennondoyle at the #sunvalleywellnessfestival in 2015 when my brother had just moved into my small condo and i helped him recover with wellness and mind body spirit connection. everyone in my life told me to use tough love but i had seen the power of sobriety and wellness from inspiring people who transformed their lives and i wanted my brother to thrive like them.

we went on to create the art business and get on the @todayshow and this summer i had the opportunity to meet rich at the mind body green conference and thank him for showing me there is so much more life to enjoy sober.
you never have to drink again
if you ask for help your life will change
both glennon and rich got treatment which is what inspired me to get help
column2: i wanted what they had and would go to any length to get it. let's end the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse in our lifetime so no one feels ashamed to get help 💓 i tried dry jan and failed and it was the best thing that ever happened to me because it made me ask for help and admit there was a problem

column1: in 5 weeks she will be 18 years old. she will be breaking multiple generational challenges. heading to graduation from high school with acceptance letters from the schools of her choice and honors!

i'm so proud of her. i'm so blessed to have her in my life. she will be the 1st in her family (on her dads side to go to college & graduate). shes graduating high school without being a teen mom out of 4 generations (or more). i'm thankful for imani in my life. it hasnt been easy the past 18 years but she gives me hope for the future!

column1: 167955;instagram;2019-01-02 05:42:37;FALSE;happy new year! isn’t that what we are supposed to say? 2018 was a year filled with some real lows. it has actually been like that for the past two years. well really
column2: i don’t think i can recall a year that wasn’t like this. i know ... i should be thankful for my health and for my many blessings. i have contemplated writing a blog or book for a long time and done nothing. in light of a very anxiety producing day
column3: i decided to create a new instagram account to share my thoughts and feelings in hopes that others in the same or similar situation as me will be able to draw some strength. sure
column4: i know i am definitely a coward keeping this in a nameless way but i am not able to do more than this today. is it a really happy new year? only time will tell. i am hoping writing will give me strength and wisdom that one day will enable me to walk away. #newyear #newyou #metoo #mystory #myfear #mystrength #myway #anxious #bebetter #livelife #befree;;en;#newyear
